Privacy Policy Team Jobs Book a Demo Privacy Policy PRIVACY POLICY We are very delighted that you have shown interest in our Data protection is of a particularly high priority for the management of the RIIICO The use of the Internet pages of the RIIICO GmbH is possible without any indication of personal data however, if a data subject wants to use special enterprise services via our website, processing of personal data could become If the processing of personal data is necessary and there is no statutory basis for such processing, we generally obtain consent from the data The processing of personal data, such as the name, address, address, or telephone number of a data subject shall always be in line with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), and in accordance with the data protection regulations applicable to the RIIICO By means of this data protection declaration, our enterprise would like to inform the general public of the nature, scope, and purpose of the personal data we collect, use and Furthermore, data subjects are informed, by means of this data protection declaration, of the rights to which they are As the controller, the RIIICO GmbH has implemented numerous technical and organizational measures to ensure the most complete protection of personal data processed through this However, data transmissions may in principle have security gaps, so absolute protection may not be For this reason, every data subject is free to transfer personal data to us via alternative means, by DEFINITIONS The data protection declaration of the RIIICO GmbH is based on the terms used by the European legislator for the adoption of the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). Our data protection declaration should be legible and understandable for the general public, as well as our customers and business To ensure this, we would like to first explain the terminology In this data protection declaration, we use, inter alia, the following terms: A) PERSONAL DATA Personal data means any information relating to an identified or identifiable natural person (âdata subjectâ). An identifiable natural person is one who can be identified, directly or indirectly, in particular by reference to an identifier such as a name, an identification number, location data, an online identifier or to one or more factors specific to the physical, physiological, genetic, mental, economic, cultural or social identity of that natural B) DATA SUBJECT Data subject is any identified or identifiable natural person, whose personal data is processed by the controller responsible for the C) PROCESSING Processing is any operation or set of operations which is performed on personal data or on sets of personal data, whether or not by automated means, such as collection, recording, organisation, structuring, storage, adaptation or alteration, retrieval, consultation, use, disclosure by transmission, dissemination or otherwise making available, alignment or combination, restriction, erasure or D) RESTRICTION OF PROCESSING Restriction of processing is the marking of stored personal data with the aim of limiting their processing in the E) PROFILING Profiling means any form of automated processing of personal data consisting of the use of personal data to evaluate certain personal aspects relating to a natural person, in particular to analyse or predict aspects concerning that natural person’s performance at work, economic situation, health, personal preferences, interests, reliability, behaviour, location or F) PSEUDONYMISATION Pseudonymisation is the processing of personal data in such a manner that the personal data can no longer be attributed to a specific data subject without the use of additional information, provided that such additional information is kept separately and is subject to technical and organisational measures to ensure that the personal data are not attributed to an identified or identifiable natural G) CONTROLLER OR CONTROLLER RESPONSIBLE FOR THE PROCESSING Controller or controller responsible for the processing is the natural or legal person, public authority, agency or other body which, alone or jointly with others, determines the purposes and means of the processing of personal data where the purposes and means of such processing are determined by Union or Member State law, the controller or the specific criteria for its nomination may be provided for by Union or Member State H) PROCESSOR Processor is a natural or legal person, public authority, agency or other body which processes personal data on behalf of the I) RECIPIENT Recipient is a natural or legal person, public authority, agency or another body, to which the personal data are disclosed, whether a third party or However, public authorities which may receive personal data in the framework of a particular inquiry in accordance with Union or Member State The following steps are identified and our current method focuses on (A) Materials, (B) Assembling, (D) Distribution and (F) End of life (which covers % of the average carbon footprint). (A) Materials Accounts for: Production of raw materials (e.g. extraction for synthetic ones, growing vegetal or animal for natural ones) of materials (e.g. extruding or molding plastics, weaving fabrics, tanning leather) NB: the assembly of the materials into the final product is step (C). On average, % of the total emissions - included in our model Emissions of materials are estimated using the weight of the pair of shoes and the proportion of the 2 main components: the upper and the outsole . We use kg as the default weight This is a bit higher than the value from ADEME s BaseImpact model for fabric shoes ( kg ) but better matches the first other values we could find (by our own measures or from LCA results shared by Caval , one of our first partner brands (average weight is kg ). NB: we still need to define a reference for weight measurements (e.g. "Size (FR) Women"). The LCA results of Caval , one of our first partner brands, measured that the upper represents on average % of the weight of their shoes, and the outsole % . Though it may not be representative of all sneakers and brands, it is for now the most accurate data we We use this as default values when the exact weight of each component cannot be The remaining unidentified materials are applied an average emission factor for shoe materials we calculated from ADEME BaseImpact LCA (B) Assembling Assembling the different materials and components of the product together into the final On average, accounts for % of the total emissions - included in our The average assembling process consumes 6 kWh . Multiplying it by the carbon intensity of the manufacturing country’s electricity gives us the carbon emissions of the (C) Upstream transport Accounts for: Transport of materials from the extraction or production site to the Transport of the materials to the assembling On average, accounts for 2 % of the total emissions - not included in our (D) Distribution Packaging and transporting the final product to the On average, accounts for % of the total emissions - included in our For now, we consider products manufactured in Asia make a long distribution trip, partly boat (87%, km), partly airplane (13%, km), since we assume our current audience reside mostly in Europe or (NB: the distribution is based on ADEME BaseImpact shoe LCA ) We use transport emission factors from EASAC Decarbonisation of transport: options and challenges report . Boat: km ((0.7+0.2) 1 ) t kgCO2eq t.km = kgCO2eq Airplane: km ((0.7+0.2) 1 ) t kgCO2eq t.km = kgCO2eq Result: % kgCO2eq + % kgCO2eq = kgCO2eq For products manufactured out of Asia, we consider they are produced closer to the consumer s We consider a 2 km truck trip on Using the same source for emission factors, the value we apply is: 2 km ((0.7+0.2 kg) 1 kg t) kgCO2eq t.km = kgCO2eq NB: the transported package weight is + kg , considering our average weight of kg and a packaging weight of kg . (E) Use On average, accounts for 0 % of the total emissions - not included in our (F) End of life Accounts for collecting, sorting, recycling or other ways of disposal (e.g. incinerating). On average, accounts for 4 % of the total emissions - included in our ADEME’s data regarding end of life solely applies to Since we target to evaluate a large array of materials and that each material has supposedly an end of life process, we chose to apply kgCO2eq if the brand doesn t enforce any recycling practice and to apply kgCO2eq when it Sources , , , March LCA Modeling and Evaluation of Consumer Products and Goods ( link ) Lynette Cheah, Natalia Duque Ciceri, Elsa Olivetti, Seiko Matsumura, Dai Forterre, Richard Roth, Randolph Kirchain, emissions reductions in footwear production, Journal of Cleaner Production, Volume , ( link ) Known limitations Shoes contain more than 2 materials

for investors to take advantage of earlier stage healthcare opportunities due to the structural, regulatory and reimbursement complexities of the healthcare Similarly, we believe the unique complexities of technology, specifically financial technology, have been highlighted by recent volatility and the continued rapid decentralization 1 . BankTech Ventures – A Venture Fund for Community Banks Skip to content BankTech Ventures The Problem The Solution The Opportunity The Team BankTech Ventures Toggle Menu BankTech Ventures Finding & Funding Solutions for Community Banks with an Unparalleled Team Free Download Watch Demo Why the Need for BankTech Ventures? The Problem Banking is facing fierce competition from all sides, including Big Tech, FinTech and challenger Veteran banks are working hard to remain competitive and deliver a positive customer experience, but are hindered by archaic legacy systems, lack of integration and antiquated As margins are compressing, the cost of operations and required investments in tech are Competitors are attracting talent which further inhibits bank The Solution Bank s expertise are safely holding deposits, transaction processing, credit allocation and regulatory The Fund will focus on investing in and providing vetted tech solutions that enhance all of the above and Banks can leverage these to develop new revenue streams, lower overhead costs, increase customer acquisition, and enhance the customer The Fund will provide investors with a tech network, strategic guidance and financial The Opportunity The banking industry is at a transformational crossroads a select few banks will adapt and many will Those that adapt and learn to leverage their charter, combined with technology, will Existing and emerging technology is changing the way banks derive revenue and make overall business The Fund s mission is to serve community banks by identifying, vetting, , and commercializing key tech for the The Team Unparalleled combination of industry experience and reach, bank technologists, and a motivation to help community banks Partnership with The Venture Center, a tech accelerator focused on FinTech and BankTech that understands how to find promising tech companies and scale Experience and infrastructure to source, test, incubate, and deploy promising technologies within GP banks, Partner banks, in order to support your bank s needs and The Problem An Evolving Industry The financial services & banking industries are impacted by evolving macro & micro trends, including: Increasing expectation that bank technology looks and feels like every other emerging tech platform, including convenience and New product offerings and asset types that challenge the tradtional banking infrastructure Aging incumbent customers and a significant wealth transfer that is shifting banking decisions to a younger generation These changes are driving a growing digital divide between technology enabled banks, Fintechs and Big These companies are gaining market share by taking customers from traditional Boston Consulting Group… “If [banks] are to survive, banks must start acting more like digital giants before digital giants… start acting like ” JPM CEO Jamie Dimon… When questioned about the threat posed by FinTechs… “Absolutely, we should be scared sh less about that… We have to We have to move ” The Solution Prudent Investment and Expansion in Tech WHAT’S NEEDED NOW? An entire redesign of many legacy processes, not just incremental Banks need to focus on their core value streams and redesign them from the front to back, with full Clients expect their banking relationship to feel like every other technology platform they interact with, and banking is currently at least one, if not two, generations The inconvenience created by legacy technology is becoming so large for customers, it is impacting their banking LEVERAGE THE RAPPORT Banks, especially community banks, already have the trust of their clients and insight into customers’ wants and The rapport is already Now banks need to meet customers where they are (on their phones and computers) to make banking as convenient and simple as possible, as well as drive revenue from other value streams (lending, payments, fraud coverage, and more). The OPPORTUNITY BankTech Ventures FINDING & FUNDING SOLUTIONS FOR COMMUNITY BANKS BankTech Ventures is a newly launched venture capital fund with the mission to invest in technology companies whose products serve community banks and their , ultimately helping drive banks’ competitiveness and growth in this evolving By leveraging BankTech Ventures’ strategic relationships within the banking and tech industries, the Fund will seek to build a portfolio of , committed tech companies, which investors can utilize for their own strategic and operational As such, the Fund intends to provide its investors the opportunity to obtain significant Research and Development spend at a much cheaper cost than if undertaken And at all times, the Fund will aim to deliver a substantially and or fully vetted vendor network, as well as strong yields to The Fund’s Sponsors and Investment Committee are comprised of veteran bankers and tech investors who have a keen eye on where both the financial and tech market are going, what constitutes a worthy vendor for community banks and the regu

I connected with an experienced real estate agent who was willing to help . What took me a month, was done in a couple of hours , and we found the perfect A few days later, I moved into my new home . This content is password To view it please enter your password below: Password:   Tebra | Build a Thriving Healthcare Practice meet tebra overview faq news + press about us contact PatientPop & Kareo are joining forces to support the connected practice of the Read more about why we’re better learn more PatientPop + Kareo Why we re merging PatientPop, a leader in practice growth technology, has joined forces with Kareo, a leader in clinical and financial software, to support the connected practice of the future and modernize every step of the patient Together, we’re committed to improving the success and wellbeing of patients and providers Practice Growth Acquire new patients with a modern website, search marketing, reputation management, and social Patient Experience Empower patients with online scheduling, appointment reminders, text messaging, digital intake, and Care Delivery Manage care delivery with a fully certified EHR to support clinical notes, prescribing and labs, and quality Billing & Payments Increase collections by automating the insurance and patient billing and payments M Patients K Healthcare Providers K Practices 1,000 Employees Frequently asked questions Why the name Tebra? To create a new and united company, we needed to create a new The name Tebra symbolizes our role as the technology backbone of practice It originates from “vertebrae,” the interlocking, parts that come together to form an essential system for bodies to Tebra will be that connected system for practices, providers, and How will PatientPop and Kareo products work together moving forward? Together as Tebra, PatientPop and Kareo will support the connected practice of the future and modernize every step of the patient Practices can already use Kareo and PatientPop together, and the two will become even more seamlessly integrated over PatientPop contributes technology to accelerate practice growth, including practice websites, online appointment booking, search marketing, digital registration, text messaging, and Kareo contributes technology to support practice operations, including a fully certified Electronic Health Record (EHR), scheduling, insurance billing, patient payments, and If you’re interested in stepping up your growth plans and being among the first to benefit from this incredible integration, get in touch to learn about adding PatientPop or Kareo (or both) to your practice Will Kareo and PatientPop continue to offer all of our current products and services? For now, nothing will change and you’ll be able to continue to use Kareo and PatientPop as you do Over time, you’ll benefit from deeper and more seamless integration between Kareo and As we begin to integrate, we’ll introduce updates and new products with However, we also remain committed to supporting and expanding integrations with healthcare technology solutions, so that both Kareo and PatientPop can continue to be used in conjunction with other I’m interested in learning how the combination of PatientPop and Kareo can benefit my What should I do next? Youthforia is It’s the moments of utter bliss you get when you re Your first lip The cute text and the screenshot sent straight to the group The waiting, the Crushes, summer break, long chats that last till 3 Getting the giggles with your best mate, hungover af, waiting for microwave mac and The lights going down before your favorite band starts Being completely in it, and taking it all Like if confetti was a That’s how how we want to make you feel with every product, every ✨ LOOKS GOOD, FEELS GOOD, DOES GOOD We’re big on having fun but we’re serious about the 🌎 The beauty industry loves fossil fuels (which makes sense because liquid plastic feels nice), but that doesn’t really work with our whole “wanting a future” That s why all of our ingredients, including synthetics, are This means we don t have to compromise on quality or We make our products biobased — each with at least % renewable ingredients (instead of fossil fuels) and our products are certified by the USDA BioPreferred We follow Green Chemistry principles (Google it, it’s super interesting!), which basically means doing what we can to make Youthforia and reduce the amount of gross, dangerous toxins we put on our face and wash down the drain (FYI, if you use products a day, that’s around chemicals made from fossil fuels now on their way to finding Nemo). Caring about and being kind to the planet is cool and important and so is using safe stuff on your ABOUT FIONA CO CHAN Youthforia was founded by Fiona Co Chan in right when COVID She kept coming back to this idea that the best part of wearing makeup is going out with your friends and sometimes that means forgetting to take your makeup She really wanted makeup that was good for your skin, so good you could sleep in During the development of Youthforia, Fiona slept in all of the lab samples (and might have recruited her husband to sleep in them too) and woke up with much better It completely changed her beauty routine philosophy - makeup is an extension of And sleeping in our lab samples is a huge part of our testing She s also passionate about Green Chemistry and not using fossil fuels and it s a big pillar of the Youthforia formulation philosophy, because most makeup contains liquid plastic and she just didn t want to do She likes making beautiful makeup that has a unique spin on existing categories while being friendly to the planet and being good for Basically, the entire Youthforia brand is just a collection of things she finds interesting to work on and is all about inspiring fun and being with your Shop Shop All Shop Value Sets Learn Clean At Youthforia Blog About About Us Rewards Brand Ambassadors Reviews Careers Student Discount Help FAQ Contact Us Refund Policy Shipping PRIVACY POLICY TERMS OF USE REFUND POLICY © FOR YOUTH LLC   Search – Youthforia Skip to content Shop All Take Our Quiz Our Story Account Your Bag (0) Continue Shopping Spend $50 more and get free shipping! Documentation – Alkimiya Hit enter to search or ESC to close Alkimiya Documentation Research Testnet What is Alkimiya? Silica Hash Vaults Architecture Components System of Smart Contract Oracle and Liquidation Bot Basis Reward Index Specifications Functions: Start a Silica contract Functions: Execute Silica Contract Functions: Settlement Functions: Default Glossary Variables Public Methods Events What is Alkimiya Introduction Alkimiya is a permissionless, protocol for consensus capital Every “consensus producer” (e.g., PoW miners, staking validators) requires continuously expending resources to participate in the mining or staking These resources are either in certain forms of computation (e.g., hashpower) or opportunity costs of liquid assets (e.g., coins staked). The primary motivation for most people to participate in consensus production is to capture the profit margin between block rewards (revenue) and the costs of resources (expense). On most networks, the costs tend to increase over time as competition heats Meanwhile, the revenue is extremely difficult to manage as it involves the fluctuations of coin price, difficulty (or equivalent metric), and network Similar to how traditional commodity producers use financial instruments to hedge against the uncertainties, consensus producers need a way to the return Alkimiya allows any consensus producers to create financial contracts backed by the underlying “consensus resources”. In , Alkimiya will focus primarily on the financial abstractions of Alkimiya has two core products: Silica and Hash Vaults . Silica Silica are commodity swaps between seller and buyer of In a traditional commodities market, a swap is a contract calling for an exchange of payments, on one or more dates, determined by the differences in two In this case, Silica represents a swap between the upfront payment that the buyer agrees to purchase the contract with and the mining rewards produced by the amount of hashpower specified during the contract Due to the nature of Silica, the seller will not receive the payment right Every day the seller delivers the required amount of mining rewards, the seller “earns” a portion of the For example, a miner running s of Ethash pays $2,000 every month for In a bear market where the miner wants to protect against the downside, the miner can issue a N Gh s over days Silica @ 2,000 USDT (N < ). Every day the miner is expected to deliver (N Reward_Per_Gh s_Per_Day) number of ETH, in exchange for a portion of the 2,000 The Basis Reward Index tracks the number of ETH s produced on a given day (see Architecture Overview ). See Specifications section for detailed calculation for the USDT “earn rate”. Hash Vaults Analogous to structured products, Hash Vaults are pools of Silica that contain additional payout In the most simple terms, HashVault can be viewed as a portfolio of It is an umbrella smart contract that holds all the Silica that the Hash Vault Admin has purchased on behalf of the buyers of the Hash The HashVault Admin can be dedicated teams running strategies, or committee members elected by a Users can pool together multiple bilateral contracts and restructure the payout logic into other forms of yield generating assets (e.g. bonds, convertibles, perpetual swap, DAO payouts). Unlike most yield generating products collateralized by a basket of coins, the cash flow of a HashVault is secured by the underlying hashpower, which represents the economic activities accrued on the Similar to Silica, buyers of Hash Vault deposit payments in exchange for VaultTokens that represent the ownership of a corresponding percentage of the rewards held in the Hash Vault at the Architecture Architecture Overview The chart below shows the core components and their main functionalities in Alkimiya Protocol . Components Silica Bilateral swap contract for Silica Account It is a factory smart contract that creates, maintains, and settles Locks mining rewards, until default liquidation or contract Maintains a list of Silica contracts it Oracle Fetches and stores information related to the Basis Reward Index for Liquidation Liquidation Engine A library of methods to perform calculations using the information from the Oracle and update the Silica Responsible for flagging Silica contracts as Default or LiquidationBot Fetches Silica Account addresses from TheGraph Calls Liquidation Engine to check the status of Silica contracts in its System of Smart Contract Silica Account The Silica Account is a factory smart contract that defines the logic for generating and tracking It is also the seller’s summary All Silica contracts with the same underlying asset (ETH, wBTC, ) is generated from the same Silica The user just needs to create a Silica Account once before selling a new asset for the first While the Silica contracts are active, the miner will deliver rewards to the Silica, where it will be held escrow until the Silica contracts are defaulted or Silica Account parameters: Asset:

Did you find our audiences via a Data Marketplace we are partnered with, like LiveRamp or Cadent, or maybe a DSP or digital buying platform? Maybe you found us through an organic search on the web or word of mouth by some colleagues or Regardless of how you heard about us, you have a story to tell and Tunnl can create and connect you with the audiences that matter most to drive your desired Tunnl’s audiences are built for organizations focused on advocacy and reputation, and used by advertisers focused on: marketing work public affairs issue advocacy corporate reputation How Does Tunnl Make Audiences? Tunnl creates audiences from four different groups of data: data library Consumer and voter information Proprietary data collection Observed media consumption data Tunnl audiences are built on our data library, which has over two decades worth of information on where Americans land on key cultural and political We marry that data with commercially available consumer and voter information to create one of the largest databases for marketing in the United The data is then enhanced with our proprietary data collected by completing hundreds of thousands of surveys per Tunnl also sits on top of several billion rows of observed media consumption behavior, which gives us a deep understanding of how Americans are consuming content across a variety of platforms and How Does All of That Data Create Targeted Audiences? We use all of this data to build probabilities on where every American adult lands on an array of issues like: climate change diversity and inclusion cryptocurrency regulation outsourcing of jobs The combination of this data allows us to build audiences of individuals who are going to be most receptive to your message, and segment them to be targeted on the screens where they are most likely to be reachable, on highly responsive and recent data that is constantly refreshed and Most importantly, Tunnl offers a seamless process to deploy our audiences across platforms where audience addressability is possible, all in a , Step 2: What Audience Options Do I Have? Tunnl has + audiences that our clients can activate against at any time, but some brands and organizations have very specific To meet that need, we also create custom audiences that are highly tailored to each client’s Audiences audiences are groups of individuals who share a similar sentiment about a certain Our audiences cover tough issues pertinent to: marketing Issue advocacy Public affairs Politics Benefits of audiences: Available immediately All cost tied to activation Drawback of audiences: No customization Custom Audiences Custom audiences are the perfect audience solution for those with niche issues and messaging needs or a larger budget that warrants control of methodology and strategy .
